						<br>
						AirAsia previously operated a fleet consisting of the Boeing 737â€“300, however, it has now completely converted to Airbus.  The current fleet is one of the youngest in the region, with an average age of 3.5 years. There are currently over 170 Airbus A320s in service and another 200 orders have been placed for the new A320neo. AirAsia has a record total of 475 narrow bodies on order with Airbus.<br>
